text.tspan: Unemployment rate, basic vs advanced education, 2017
Unemployment rate for individuals, age 25-54, who have an advanced education vs those who have a basic
education. Basic education includes primary and lower secondary, while advanced education can refer to short-cycle
tertiary education, Bachelor's, Master's, or Doctoral level study. See source tab for more details.
